properties.areaDesc: Delaware Bay waters south of East Point NJ to Slaughter Beach DE; Delaware Bay waters north of East Point NJ to Slaughter Beach DE
properties.headline: Storm Warning issued February 7 at 7:21AM EST until February 7 at 6:00PM EST by NWS Mount Holly NJ
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest winds 25 to 35 kt with gusts up to 50 kt and
extremely rough waters.

* WHERE...Delaware Bay waters north of East Point NJ to
Slaughter Beach DE and Delaware Bay waters south of East Point
NJ to Slaughter Beach DE.

* WHEN...Until 6 PM EST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Very strong winds will cause hazardous seas which
could capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...An initial surge of strong southerly or
southwesterly winds is expected mid to late morning. A second
surge of strong westerly winds is expected early this
afternoon. Gale force gusts may linger through at least
midnight as winds gradually subside.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should remain in port, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM EST THIS EVENING
